Phantom-WG Modern — Update Guide
==================================

Standard Update:
  ./tools/prod.sh update

  This pulls the latest code from upstream and restarts all services.
  Environment files (.env.daemon, .env.auth-service) are always preserved.

  Alternatively:
    git pull
    ./tools/prod.sh restart

Compose Lock:
  If you have modified docker-compose.yml locally (custom ports,
  resource limits, extra volumes), protect your changes with compose lock:

    ./tools/prod.sh compose lock

  Once locked, every future update preserves your local docker-compose.yml.
  The lock persists across sessions — set it once and forget it.

    ./tools/prod.sh compose status    Check if locked
    ./tools/prod.sh compose unlock    Release to pull upstream changes

  How it works:
    Compose lock uses git update-index --skip-worktree to tell git
    to ignore local changes to docker-compose.yml during pull.

Dependency Updates:
  If requirements.txt or the Dockerfile changed after an update:

    ./tools/prod.sh rebuild
    ./tools/prod.sh restart

  This rebuilds the Docker image from scratch with new dependencies.

Version Check:
  ./tools/prod.sh show-versions

  Shows the current daemon version and bridge versions running
  inside the container.

Rollback:
  To roll back to a previous version:

    git fetch --tags
    git checkout v1.0.7
    ./tools/prod.sh restart

  If the Dockerfile may have changed between versions, rebuild first:

    git checkout v1.0.7
    ./tools/prod.sh rebuild
    ./tools/prod.sh restart

  This creates a detached HEAD state — you are pinned to that tag.
  To resume receiving updates, switch back to main:

    git checkout main
    ./tools/prod.sh update

  Environment files and runtime data are unaffected by rollback.

Hard Reset:
  ./tools/prod.sh hard-reset

  Destroys ALL data: secrets, auth database, client databases,
  and Docker volumes. Requires typing 'yes' to confirm.

  After hard reset, run setup again:
    ./tools/prod.sh setup

What Gets Preserved on Update:
  .env.daemon                Always preserved (not tracked by git)
  .env.auth-service          Always preserved (not tracked by git)
  docker-compose.yml         Preserved only when compose lock is active
  container-data/            Always preserved (runtime data, not in git)

What Gets Updated:
  phantom_daemon/            Daemon source code
  services/auth-service/     Auth service source
  services/react-spa/dist/   Web dashboard build
  services/nginx/            Reverse proxy config
  tools/                     Production CLI and libraries
  Dockerfile                 Image definition
  requirements.txt           Python dependencies